g.text: │ Themes are an easy way to style a rich-click CLI. │
│ As an end-user of CLIs, you can set the RICH_CLICK_THEME= env var to │
│ style all rich-click CLIs you use. │
│ As a developer, you can add a theme to your CLI with one line of code: │
│ Themes consist of Color Palettes and Formats, which can be mixed and │
│ matched: The name of a full theme has the following schema: │
│ For example, the forest-slim theme uses the forest color palette and │
│ nord ▓▓ ▓▓ ▓▓ Many shades of cool colors │
│ cargo ▓▓ ▓▓ ▓▓ Cargo CLI theme; legible and bold │
│ forest ▓▓ ▓▓ ▓▓ Earthy tones with analogous colors │
│ news ▓▓ ▓▓ ▓▓ Simple red accented theme (white and │
│ mono ▓▓ ▓▓ Monochromatic theme with no colors │
│ ✓ box (Default) Original rich-click format with boxes │
│ slim Simple, classic, no-fuss CLI format │
│ nu Great balance of compactness, legibility, and style │
